Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.62,0:23:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,was there what was said what secular influences must have come in because the\Nlevel of truth of Christianity dropped from the 900s down to jobs several
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.77,0:23:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,hundred points after the Council of Nicaea so some grave error came in there\Nand corrupted the original purity of the original truth that did not happen in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.77,0:23:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhism Buddhism has taught is still a\Nin the 900s so very little has been lost but other other others have gone
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.63,0:24:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,down considerably and some of the world's religions which I don't want to\Neven mention have become actually fallen below 200 in the negative range and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.41,0:24:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,become sort of cults so a lot of religions were then corrupted by cultism\Nsee so when people study the history of spirituality they really are coming
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.07,0:24:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from a very naive viewpoint to look at it like that.\Nthey look at it like studying history most of the Christian churches constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.33,0:24:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,repeat historical documents which first of all are not even accurate if you can\Ncalibrate them yourself you can see they're not accurate at all and now they
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.07,0:24:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,become ingrained in our society and revered so here you've got falsehood\Nrevered in our society and passed down generation after generation so I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.45,0:24:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to discover you know what is impeded the development of the\Nman's consciousness throughout time. That is really what I'm addressing in this
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.95,0:25:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,particular book. And we will address some sacred cows. We will look at some sacred\Ncows. And I'm getting old enough so I don't care what they do to me. Now is a good time to do it. I'm getting older anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.71,0:25:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I got shot for the Enterprise. I'm just kidding, but we will address some\Nsacred cows. Because why does ignorance prevail century after century?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.99,0:25:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Such profound ignorance blinds mankind. You know, mankind is just newly sprouted,\Nnewly sprouted. And what prevails primarily is profound ignorance in just
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.34,0:25:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,about every level of human endeavor. Modern society only started a couple\Nhundred years ago. I mean in time it's like yesterday. So, how does such
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.44,0:25:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,profound\Nignorance prevail century after century? Modern society only started a couple hundred years ago. I mean in time it's like yesterday. So, how does such profound
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.08,0:25:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,ignorance prevail century after century? Modern society only started a couple hundred years ago. I mean in time it's like yesterday. So, how does such\Nignorance prevail century after century? Modern society only started a couple hundred years ago. I mean in time it's like yesterday. So, how does such
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.08,0:25:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,ignorance prevail century after century? Modern society only started a couple hundred years ago. I mean in time it's like yesterday. So, how does such\Nignorance prevail century after century? Modern society only started a couple hundred years ago. I mean in time it's like yesterday. So, how does such
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.31,0:25:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,ignorance prevail century after century? Modern society only started a couple hundred years ago. I mean in time it's like yesterday. So, how does such\Nignorance prevail century after century? Modern society only started a couple hundred years ago. I mean in time it's like yesterday. So, how does such
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.31,0:26:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,ignorance prevail century after century? Modern society only started a couple hundred years ago. I mean in time it's like yesterday. So, how does such\Nis it suddenly stopped? We don't all still think the world is flat, do we? Do we? She thinks the world is flat. She thinks the world is flat, but the rest of us don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.81,0:26:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, when it comes to spirituality and religion, most people still think the world is flat. I mean, that's really their level of understanding. It's nowhere, nowhere at all.\NSo, we are going to, in this particular study we're doing now, address the evolution of consciousness throughout all of mankind, mankind's history, and try to track out why and what is holding it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.89,0:27:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, how come it's not up to 300, you know, 400? What's keeping it, why isn't it 500? Why isn't the unconditional love prevailing in our society? Why doesn't it?\NSo, that's the kind of things that we're...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.08,0:27:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at right now.\NAlright, so I guess we're all reassembled this afternoon so we can resume.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.20,0:27:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was talking about the nature of consciousness as the evolution of consciousness is experienced through this particular track of historical memory here.\NAnd one thing that was peculiar, the other thing that was peculiar about the sudden presence was
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.22,0:28:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the feeling of completion, the feeling of not needing anything more.\NAnd that prevails to this day. If somebody says, what do you want for Christmas? I have to think, what does want mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.02,0:28:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's really meaningless. There's no wanting anything. There's no lack, there's no need, there's no desire.\NJanuary 10th, 1965, when I really got hit by the presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.12,0:28:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,at that moment, in that moment,\Nall that's considered essentially human disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.47,0:28:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Desire for fame, fortune, money, power, influence over others,\Nall these strange melodies that afflict people seemed to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.08,0:28:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They just disappeared. It wasn't through any kind of heroic spiritual effort.\NThey disappeared of their own nature and have not reappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.56,0:28:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nthen I was left in the world devoid of what drives most people,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.56,0:29:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and trying to figure out what to do from here.\NWhat do you do from here? Well, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.75,0:29:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And people would say, well, you've got to pay attention to reality,\Nand get back to practice, and make some money, and all this kind of thing, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.88,0:29:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And it didn't make too much sense to me.\NI understood the words, sort of, but it didn't ever have any,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.88,0:29:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there wasn't any inner reality for it to hang into, to activate you.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.00,0:29:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be anxious about your own survival to worry about such things.\NBut, anyway, over some years that I retired from the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.51,0:29:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I did relearn how to relate to the world,\Nand one handy way of doing that was watching television.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.80,0:29:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't own a television set.\NI didn't read newspapers or magazines or any such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.92,0:29:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just spent all the time meditating.\NAnd I discovered that if you watch TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.28,0:30:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you can find out what's been happening in the world the last ten years, or whatever.\NI remember there was Princess something-or-other.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.72,0:30:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She was very famous on the front page of everything that went in the grocery store.\NThere she was in front of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.72,0:30:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know who that she was, or any of those people.\NSo there was a relearning of how to be in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.85,0:30:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When those things happen, people say,\Nwell, what is that like when it happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.56,0:30:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In the high 500s, you go into this incredible being in love with everyone.\NAnd you go through the phase of crying at the drop of a hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.56,0:30:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at two people looking at each other tenderly,\Nthe love just knocks you out, and you start to weep.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.91,0:30:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you go through a stage of crying and weeping over beauty,\Nand you hear a piece of music, and it just lays you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.91,0:30:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We were speaking someplace or other,\Nand she turned on the TV, and this incredible symphony,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.26,0:31:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible music came on, and I just lay on the bed.\NI couldn't get off the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.45,0:31:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The beauty was so knocking.\NIt just knocked you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.45,0:31:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's that.\NIn the high 500s, the realization of the beauty and the perfection of all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.45,0:31:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing shines forth.\NThe intrinsic beauty of each thing shines forth in its radiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.45,0:31:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes you weep with its beauty.\NAnd so there is that difficulty.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.10,0:31:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In monasteries and places like that, it's common.\NSometimes they cry for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.13,0:31:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say anything nice to them or loving or show them a rose or something,\Nthey're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.13,0:31:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't rely on them to get much work done.\NSo the high 500s, you see the beauty and the perfection of all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.68,0:32:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And everything knocks you out.\NThere's a period of time where everything knocks you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.00,0:32:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're not careful, even that knocks you out.\NSo you see a little tree or a weed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.03,0:32:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The average person would say that's just a weed.\NBut what you see is the incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.03,0:32:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the weed as a magnificent sculpture.\NYou see its incredible beauty and perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.03,0:32:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the incredible perfection of the weed standing forth.\NAnd you see the design of each thing shining forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.09,0:32:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So the intrinsic beauty of creation shines forth.\NAnd the perfection of all things sort of takes hold in the high 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.08,0:32:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at 600, you run into sort of the near death experience kind of experience I had\Nwhere the intensity of the bliss is such you cannot function.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.08,0:32:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot function.\NThere is no need to eat, drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.15,0:33:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The body functions just come to a halt.\NThere's only the radiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.76,0:33:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And because you're outside of time, there's no way of knowing whether weeks, months,\Nor whether it's even the same lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.49,0:33:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You sound crazy, but you don't even know if it's the same lifetime.\NAnd whether you survive or not really depends on having people around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.52,0:33:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, if it weren't for the presence of a loving, if it wasn't for Susan,\NI probably wouldn't even eat for weeks at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.91,0:33:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NIt just never comes to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.91,0:33:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It just doesn't come to mind.\NAnd so it's good if you do intense spiritual work to be aligned with a spiritual group.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.80,0:33:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Be aligned with a spiritual group.\NBecause any spiritual practice you do, you can just suddenly take off.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.80,0:33:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NBecause spiritual evolution is both longitudinal like this, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.80,0:33:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of like, you know, the Dow Jones or something.\NAs the years go by, you go ups and downs and ups and downs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.96,0:34:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And you gradually evolve higher and higher.\NAnd then there's sudden breaks where you suddenly go that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.99,0:34:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You can suddenly go vertically just like that.\NYou can be playing with a mantra that somebody, some great guru whispered in your ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.15,0:34:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get $350, you get $550 or whatever.\NAnd all your life you're out there waiting in the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.24,0:34:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden, bam, instantly, you're out of this.\NAnd if you're out by yourself and nobody knows what's going on with you, they could think he's going catatonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.47,0:34:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,One time I went catatonic.\NI mean, I went like that in this divine bliss state.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.47,0:34:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw the world would think he's catatonic.\NAnd they would take me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.47,0:34:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, that's all right.\NI surrendered that one to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.47,0:34:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care if they think I'm catatonic.\NAnd they're going to haul you off to a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.47,0:34:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sitting on a rock.\NI'm meditating.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.47,0:34:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in this bliss state.\NAnd I couldn't get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.04,0:35:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, well, they'll see this person sitting there.\NAnd they'll call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.04,0:35:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's OK.\NAnd the police will take you to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.04,0:35:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's OK.\NAnd the doctor will examine you and say, he's catatonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.04,0:35:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, OK.\NAnd then they will put you in a mental hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.04,0:35:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, that's all right.\NAnd they'll probably shoot you full of Thorazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.04,0:35:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all right, too.\NBecause that which I am is not reachable by Thorazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.04,0:35:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You can sedate the hell out of the body and the mind.\NBut I'm not the body and the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.04,0:35:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't care what you do with it.\NYou see how you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.04,0:35:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're like beyond all.\NWell, if you didn't have friends around to see that you ate and got off the rock, you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.04,0:35:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,could still eat.\NYou could still be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.04,0:35:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I'm kidding.\NBut you know, after Ramana Maharshi, Ramana Maharshi was 15 or 16 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.04,0:35:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was just an ordinary religious Hindu fellow.\NNot overly religious or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.04,0:35:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And one day, he suddenly felt like he was dying.\NAnd he fell down in a weak state.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.43,0:36:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And he realized he had just died.\NWell, then he went into this state of bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.52,0:36:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this state of bliss, he just sat there, I guess, for some days and weeks and was all\Nbitten up by insects and hadn't eaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.55,0:36:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was discovered by some people who did have some spiritual erudition and recognized\Nthe state he was in.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.84,0:36:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was unable to speak.\NHe didn't even talk for two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.84,0:36:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It took him two years to relearn how to talk.\NAnd so if he had not been surrounded by a couple of spiritual, spiritually oriented
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.12,0:36:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,people, you know, I guess they could have put him in a mental hospital in India for\Nadvanced serious catatonia or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.50,0:36:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to have some people who know what you're doing, you know, because it can happen\Nany time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.50,0:36:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Just why?\NBecause your spiritual orientation is to go in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.50,0:36:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you are what makes the technique work.\NIt isn't the mantra that gets you to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.11,0:37:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the spinning the prayer wheel or getting funny haircuts, sitting cross-legged\Nand breathing in strange and peculiar ways from one side of the nose to the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.11,0:37:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless it.\NIt's because of who you are and your intention that that should get you to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.11,0:37:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what gets you to God.\NAnd in Ramana Maharshi it says, God feels sorry for you after a while and picks you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.71,0:37:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,up and takes you into his arms.\NAfter all that strange breathing and staring at the sun and starving yourself and ringing
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.71,0:37:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,bells and chanting mantras and all this weird stuff, the strange haircuts, all the bizarre\Nthings, and the bells and whistles that goes with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.96,0:37:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So those are not what's divine.\NWhat's divine is the entity that is empowering those things to bring them closer to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.02,0:37:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,See people going to the holy land.\NImagine how holy that holy land is right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.02,0:38:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,After all the killing, warfare, bloodshed, murder, hatred, loathing, persecution, all\Nin the name of this holy place.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.02,0:38:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I never calculated the energy of it.\NI'd be afraid to.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.02,0:38:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine what the energy of the holy place is in this earth or life.\NLike God's interested in real estate, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.46,0:38:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This little strip of this country is holy to God, you know.\NSo one of the things we want to do in the Eye of the Eye is improve God's reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.56,0:38:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of my functions here, according to, just to clear up his name on me.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.48,0:38:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because God gets blamed for all the negativity in the world, don't you understand?\NThe God of retaliation, the God of fear, the God of jealousy, hatred, and anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.60,0:38:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This map of consciousness we have over on one side, the view of God that that particular\Nlevel of consciousness is agreeable with.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.66,0:39:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NIf your level of consciousness is way down at the bottom, then a God who's angry at you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.66,0:39:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and vengeful because he's got low self-esteem.\NAnd gets upset if you worship graven images or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.79,0:39:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And strikes you dead in your whole city.\NBurns it up and fit of paranoid jealousy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.97,0:39:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You lose control of himself.\NDestroys whole cities and civilizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.97,0:39:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There, take that.\NBut, you know, most of the world believes in God like that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.73,0:39:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I start these lectures, usually, usually I have this map of consciousness and a transparency,\Nwhich I forgot the date.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.86,0:39:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.\NProjected up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.86,0:39:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first thing I bring to people's attention is that God is at the top of the chart.\NNot at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.92,0:39:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And people say, oh, that's ridiculous.\NOh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.92,0:39:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the world believes that God is at the bottom of the chart.\NThe God of vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.02,0:39:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of hatred.\NThe God of anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.02,0:40:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The God that's paranoid.\NThat needs, uh, it goes to Thorazine to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.12,0:40:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Worried that his power is being undermined by people with all their strange rituals and\Nstuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.40,0:40:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You eat meat on Friday, I mean, you know, or whatever.\NYou don't wear a certain kind of hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.49,0:40:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you do wear a certain kind of hat.\NImagine Jesus getting upset because you wore a hat in church or you didn't wear a hat in
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.68,0:40:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,church.\NWhen I was young, all the ladies had to wear a hat in church.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.68,0:40:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because God would be upset if you didn't wear a, if ladies didn't wear a hat in church.\NIt was sacrilegious.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.10,0:40:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sacrilegious.\NOh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.36,0:40:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So there we got all that negativity, you know, incorporated into our culture.\NIt's sacrilegious.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.36,0:40:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, God's gonna be upset with you.\NLike, God's gonna be upset with you if you wear a hat or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.54,0:40:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't even know if you're wearing a hat, you know.\NBut, if you like to think that God does notice that you're wearing a hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.70,0:40:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the hat that you're wearing, so how would he notice it?\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.70,0:41:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is can't notice its own self, isness, because isness is isness, and not that which\Nwitnesses isness.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.92,0:41:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NIdentity knows only its own identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.21,0:41:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore comprehend what God is all about when I say that.\NUnderstand that identity is its own identity and nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.63,0:41:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing arises as a creation out of its own essence.\NEach thing is complete and total and perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.45,0:41:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so then that, if that is so, then what?\NWhat goes on with human consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.48,0:41:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it not so for all of us?\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.48,0:41:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to talk today a little bit about karma, karma.\NAnother thing I want to address in the book I'm working on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.01,0:41:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at the spiritual ignorance that goes on,\Nyou see ignorance in all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.01,0:41:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And we said the world is flat.\NA lot of people still believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.01,0:41:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Not too many people.\NBut in religion and spirituality, a lot of people are really at the level of thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.01,0:42:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is flat.\NThat there's been no examination, reexamination of things that are passed down generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.01,0:42:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's like it's, you know, passed down.\NTherefore it's, it's written in rock, you know, written in eternal cement.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.81,0:42:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because some prophet said it someplace or other and it was misquoted and now it's not\Nprevailed as law.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.26,0:42:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Not prevailed as law.\NSo mankind then is held by fallacious laws that he believes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.09,0:42:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Fallacious belief systems.\NWhen you calibrate the energy fields of what prevails in mankind's spiritual belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.73,0:42:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it will, you'll feel like training.\NThe beliefs in things that are just grossly negative, just grossly make your arm go weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.02,0:42:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is profound.\NSo fallacy then gains its influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.95,0:42:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,By repetition.\NBy ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.75,0:43:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,By not knowing the difference between truth and falsehood.\NNot knowing the difference between truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.75,0:43:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that's true should certainly stand up to kinesiologic test of truth, yes?\NSame thing should go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.42,0:43:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We would say at least it's not exactly up to snuff.\NA lot of what goes on in the world does not come up to snuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.80,0:43:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does all this perpetuate itself then, generation after generation?\NWe'd have to look at how does consciousness transmit itself from lifetime to lifetime?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.96,0:43:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'd have to look at what has historically been called karma.\NNow, karma is one thing and reincarnation is another.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.81,0:43:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When people get into discussions, they confuse the two.\NWhen we talk about karma, we're not talking about reincarnation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.81,0:43:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a different subject.\NTo re-embody oneself is...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.81,0:44:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,a different subject.\NKarma has to do with consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.26,0:44:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with embodiment.\NAll the world's religions teach karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.28,0:44:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All the world's religions.\NThey don't call it karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.28,0:44:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity, the world, doesn't use the word karma.\NBut Jesus Christ says that you shall reap as you sow.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.28,0:44:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He certainly tells you to avoid sin because the consequences are not too great.\NAnd warns us that below 200
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.05,0:44:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,will take you into unfortunate places when you leave the body.\NAnd all the world's great spiritual traditions and religions all teach the one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.24,0:44:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That the choices we make, the options we make,\Nwill determine
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.88,0:44:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,future experience of that aspect of the human which survives its physicality.\NThere's no question that...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.88,0:45:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in traditional Buddhism,\NChristianity, there is no mention of other than one...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.33,0:45:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a presumption you only have one body.\NAnd then, after you leave this body,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.43,0:45:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you will go someplace befitting what your choices in this world determine for yourself.\NHeaven, hell, purgatory, or limbo, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.43,0:45:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There aren't many other places that cover this.\NThere are options when you leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.43,0:45:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, herein comes the fear of the Christian then,\Nthat there will be a great judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.71,0:45:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And this judge may take a very negative view of your behaviors in this lifetime.\NAnd the consequences will be unpleasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.71,0:45:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have this negative God that we fear will judge us at the end.\NThis God is external to the reality of who we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.34,0:45:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because to be judged by God,\Nyou would have to be this and God would have to be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.69,0:46:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that implies a separation.\NThere would have to be a separation between the reality of that which you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.69,0:46:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,this kind of entity that sits out there and judges you,\Nand then takes action against you via force.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.69,0:46:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because throwing people into hell with a fry is sort of force, isn't it?\NNot exactly friendly, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.20,0:46:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there is a presumption and a separation,\Nand the projection of man's own negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.52,0:46:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, Sigmund Freud,\Nand Moses and Amathia,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.59,0:46:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Sigmund Freud calibrates at 499,\Nhe correctly deduced that the negative images of God
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.81,0:46:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,were projections of man's own unconscious guilt and fear.\NAnd he said, because they're just projections from the unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.32,0:46:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they have no reality.\NAnd there he was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.36,0:46:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But then he made the error.\NHe said, therefore, there is no God.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.36,0:47:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was a jump.\NWhat he should have said is,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.36,0:47:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,these projections from man's unconscious\Ncreate a false image of God as a very negative being,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.45,0:47:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and that particular being doesn't have reality.\NNo, he didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.45,0:47:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's why Freud stands at 499.\NCarl Jung, who calibrates at 520,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.45,0:47:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,validated the reality of man's spirit.\NSo, 499 is the great barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.84,0:47:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very, very unusual and very hard to get over 499,\Nand not many people do.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.03,0:47:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the great intellect stopped at 499,\Nbecause there's a jump to a different paradigm of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.60,0:47:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to jump from the linear to the nonlinear.\NYou have to see the reality of the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.60,0:47:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Carl Jung, who calibrates at about 520,\Nvalidated the spiritual reality of man,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.67,0:47:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore calibrates an entire Freud.\NWell, the God that Freud threw out
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.76,0:47:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,was the same one I threw out\Nwhen I saw the totality of man's suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.76,0:48:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I threw out any God that could be the cause of that.\NSo, the misunderstanding was
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.76,0:48:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was ascribing to God, blaming God\Nfor that which is the creation of the human ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.76,0:48:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the human ego that creates war and pestilence and suffering\Nand all the miseries that we blame on God.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.76,0:48:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When you understand the nature of God,\Nthe thought that negativity could be some kind of a weird reality
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.81,0:48:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that emanates from that divinity is absurd.\NBut when people have had no personal experience of the presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.81,0:48:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,they are willing to believe almost anything that you tell them.\NAnd they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.81,0:48:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What does determine then what happens at death?\NWhat is the spirit all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.60,0:48:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we said that everything and anything on the planet\Ngives forth an energy and a vibration of frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.66,0:48:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We can calibrate that frequency.\NWe can calibrate the frequency and energy of anything and everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.66,0:49:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,every saint that ever lived,\Nevery sentence pronounced by every guru who ever lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.33,0:49:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of truth of that\Nthought.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.66,0:49:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, all of us are carried with us a spiritual body,\Nthe frequency of which is actually calibratable.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.66,0:49:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And its fate depends then completely on what its calibrated energy level is.\NSo I want to give you a different picture of causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.98,0:49:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a different picture of how the universe works.\NEach thing, because it is only what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.27,0:49:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it is not what it is because of something else,\Nbut only because of its own essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.48,0:49:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only...\NYou only...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.48,0:49:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It is what it is out of its expression of its divinity\Nexpressing itself as what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.48,0:49:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's...\NThe way the universe is working is not like linear causality
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.88,0:50:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,where a billion balls are hitting each other.\NInstead, it's almost like little tiny magnets
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.43,0:50:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,all circulating around in a great big vast space.\NAnd the movement and the direction and the influences
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.84,0:50:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,are all emanating from the essence of what each thing is\Nin and of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.84,0:50:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?\NIt's like its polarity, its power,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.36,0:50:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is interacting with the field.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.09,0:50:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Like little iron filings in a giant electromagnetic field.\NEach filing lines itself up depending on its polarity,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.09,0:50:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,its degree of energy,\Nhow much iron is in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.09,0:50:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the power of the field.\NThere's no arbitrary field knocking this little magnet this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.38,0:50:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad little magnet knocking it.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.73,0:50:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is being where it is\Nbecause out of the essence of its own divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.73,0:50:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it cannot be otherwise.\NEach thing is expressing itself
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.89,0:51:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and like a cloud floats through the atmosphere\Ndepending on the geometric pressure and the winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.21,0:51:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which is the spirit body\Nand, of course, at least the physical body,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.21,0:51:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody experiences their own physical death.\NI might as well tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.21,0:51:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody experiences their own physical death.\NThe moment of death, wham, you're out of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.11,0:51:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You witness the body laying there\Nand the car just ran over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.11,0:51:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of interesting, but not too.\NAnd anything catastrophic you experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.80,0:51:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not dying.\NIt's horribly painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.15,0:51:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.\NIf it's fatal,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.65,0:51:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,yep, you're out in an instant.\NYou witness it happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.65,0:51:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what happens to you?\NWell, now what happens to you depends on the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.65,0:51:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the frequency and the vibration of where you are.\NYou're now a cloud in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.65,0:51:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will automatically\Ngravitate to the energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.68,0:51:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which is your natural space to be in, right?\NSo if we can say,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.68,0:52:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,if the heavens calibrate just like this,\Nand they do, the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.68,0:52:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates the same way,\Nyou will gravitate to where,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.68,0:52:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,say, everybody is like a cork in the water.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.97,0:52:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You rise to the level of your own buoyancy.\NThere's no arbitrary god out there
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.36,0:52:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,pushing this cork to go there.\NEach cork, when you think of what would
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.36,0:52:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,divine justice be,\Ndivine justice would have to be absolutely perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.36,0:52:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing automatically,\Nbecause of its own nature
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.48,0:52:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and the nature of the universe,\Nis exactly where it is due to
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.48,0:52:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,its own expression of its own nature.\NUnderstand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.48,0:52:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That is absolute,\Nthe divinity of,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.74,0:52:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the justice of God,\Nthat only that which you have
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.47,0:52:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,absolutely deserved of yourself,\Ncan possibly be.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.47,0:52:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing arbitrary outside of yourself\Nhas any influence over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.47,0:53:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, just from the viewpoint\Nof the science of consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.84,0:53:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,then,\Nthe negative gods
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.84,0:53:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,have no power over you whatsoever,\Nbecause, first of all, they have no existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.84,0:53:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of us determines their own fate,\Ntheir own future.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.84,0:53:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So every choice that we make\Nfrom moment to moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.84,0:53:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,then,\Nchanges the buoyancy of our cork.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.68,0:53:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So if our Holy Spirit is like a\Netheric cork,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.66,0:53:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it goes where it's going to go in the universe,\Nbecause of its own buoyancy,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.66,0:53:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,its own power,\Nits own frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.66,0:53:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, a spirit that radiates at 500\Nis going to go to a different place
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.82,0:53:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,than a spirit that radiates at 190.\N190 is probably going to land in a space
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.04,0:54:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,where there's militarism\Nand war and pridefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.17,0:54:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And so each spirit's going to be\Nwhere it needs to go,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.91,0:54:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,where it wants to go.\NIt's going to go where it is decided
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.91,0:54:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by its own actions to go.\NIf that is so,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.42,0:54:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,then,\Nthe drama that we see that goes on
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.68,0:54:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in the human evolution of society, then,\Nis the outcropping,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.68,0:54:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the acting out of these levels of consciousness.\NTo get over 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.73,0:54:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to cross the line.\NYou have to cross over the level of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.73,0:54:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity.\NThat's a big one.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.73,0:54:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of the population is below 200.\NHow do you get above 200?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.10,0:54:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,200 means out of integrity,\Nout of integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.77,0:54:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,out of integrity,\Ncommitment, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.00,0:54:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One is even willing to give up their life\Nfor something greater than the personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.00,0:55:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we see war is the great opportunity\Nfor spirits to come back,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.06,0:55:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,walk into a rain of bullets,\Nbecause they believe in the divinity of the emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.57,0:55:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the kamikaze pilots all went\Nto a great place when they left.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.89,0:55:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You willingly give up your body,\Nor the faith that you believe is God,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.12,0:55:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because they thought the emperor was\Nthe representation of the sun god.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.12,0:55:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NYou cross over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.24,0:55:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You cross over 200.\NYou come out of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.24,0:55:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and you cross over 200,\Nand you want integrity for eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.24,0:55:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's true.\NWe just said it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.44,0:55:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We just said it's true.\NI just knew intuitively, spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.72,0:55:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the kamikaze pilots, you know,\Nwhen you see them,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.72,0:55:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for each other,\Nfor the love of themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.13,0:55:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for their love of each other and their country,\Nand for the love of their emperor,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.13,0:55:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they surrender their actual life\Nfor that which they believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.13,0:56:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's a profound spiritual step.\NWe don't care what it means politically,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.96,0:56:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,now we're talking spiritually.\NSpiritually, it's a profound step.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.96,0:56:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see all that goes on\Nin the human endeavor, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.09,0:56:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is really an opportunity\Nfor the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.09,0:56:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There is some point in the evolution\Nof your own consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.09,0:56:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Every man here who can remember past lives\Nwill remember a lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.86,0:56:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you had to stand up,\Nwalk out of the trenches,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.86,0:56:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and face certain death.\NAnd you had to do it for the emperor,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.86,0:56:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you had to do it for Nero,\Nyou had to do it for the Roman Empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.21,0:56:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you had to do it for Christ, whatever.\NAnd that moment is a profound moment
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.50,0:56:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because you cross over.\NAnd, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.50,0:56:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,when people go over 600,\Nthey tend to remember past lives, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.95,0:56:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about karma.\NSo, anyway, past lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.95,0:56:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I find it difficult how people can have\Na really profound, solid spiritual understanding
