Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.32,1:12:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not telling him what to do.\NWe're not telling him anything that's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.40,1:13:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think there's anything wrong with his society at all.\NHis society has evolved to a certain point,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.22,1:13:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is what it is,\Nbecause that's what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.04,1:13:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It is what it is at this point.\NBut we as a group can certainly potentiate its growth,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.00,1:13:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's what we're going to do.\NAll in agreement?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.58,1:13:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All in favor of turning China around?\NAnybody opposed?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.61,1:13:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Greatest thing that ever happened in Chinese history\Nhas just happened in this room.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.71,1:13:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't know it yet.\NWe're not going to tell them.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.19,1:13:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not going to tell them,\Nbecause that would set up a defense, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.39,1:13:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want to set up a defense, see?\NSo if we said, we as a group are praying for you,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.05,1:13:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to help you people,\Nit would set up enormous resistance there.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.29,1:13:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are these goddamn Americans trying to tell us how to end the crisis?\NWe were civilized by then.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.11,1:13:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You people were still hanging around in trees,\Nyou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.89,1:13:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If I was a Chinaman, I'd say,\Nwhat, that's what folks were still hanging in trees,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.73,1:14:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,for God's sake, aren't we?\NSo you see how the American attitude sets other people on edge.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.39,1:14:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of a little embarrassing, you know what I'm saying?\NA little embarrassing at times.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.41,1:14:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see the lack of humility,\Ntalking to a great leader with great potentiality,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.85,1:14:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to move his people.\NI saw it happen in North Korea, so I know it can happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.01,1:14:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also know that we have the capacity to do that with China.\NLet's see if we do.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.10,1:14:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I just said it so much, China.\NWe can raise the level of the consciousness of the leader of China
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.16,1:14:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,by over 10 points' resist, by 20 points' resist,\Nby 30 points' resist, holy Christ, by 50 points' resist, oh my God.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.80,1:14:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So this group, they're, you know, not necessarily meditation.\NWhile you're buttering your toast, you can just think,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.28,1:14:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,gosh, you're not such a bad guy.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.92,1:14:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You butter your toast.\NIt says that we can raise his level of consciousness 40 points.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.28,1:14:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enormous, enormous, 40 points.\N30.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.93,1:14:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an incredible jump.\NAnyway, it would.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.24,1:15:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we being grandiose?\NAre we being real?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.30,1:15:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're being real.\NSee, what happens is you deny your own divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.06,1:15:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?\NYou see, I'm not of divine essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.12,1:15:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just an ego.\NWhat allows you to be an ego?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.11,1:15:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,People like me, they wouldn't have the power\Nto influence the future of a giant, the biggest country on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.31,1:15:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chinese are what, one and a half billion people\Nor two billion people or something out of the six billion that exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.20,1:15:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, this little group of people here in nowhere California,\Nthey're going to shift the whole .
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.40,1:15:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?\NWhy not?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.12,1:15:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the miraculous, there's nothing to the miraculous.\NThe miraculous is the obvious.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.45,1:15:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The miraculous is the way that it wants to go.\NThe miraculous is what brought us together and brought up this subject so that we should do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.28,1:16:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,God said, gee, I need a group to get together and help out China there.\NHow about you bringing it up, Dave, at your next talk?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.17,1:16:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIt only came to me as I said it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.63,1:16:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,See, I never know what I'm going to say.\NI hear it as it's said.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.81,1:16:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no knowing that it's going to be said.\NAnd usually there's no recognition that it was said.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.89,1:16:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I depend on her to recall that.\NBut that which erupts of its own is out of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.83,1:16:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?\NYou can tell by the energy of it that it's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.95,1:16:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so.\NThe collective power of the divinity within each and every one of us
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.20,1:16:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,expressed out as love towards that country and its leader will have a profound influence.\NThat's for certain.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.01,1:16:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,To deny it is to deny your own reality.\NIt's to say, I'm only a weak ego and I have no influence in this world.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.29,1:17:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just a nothing.\NI'm just a toad.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.29,1:17:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's not so.\NEach one of us here reflects the divinity of God expressed through our own beingness in this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.46,1:17:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good karma time, folks.\NPut this one, wrap this one up for eternity.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.38,1:17:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get there, you can say, yep, we were part of what pulled the chain out of the mud, you know, and got them sailing again.\NNo, it's just the joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.17,1:17:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the joy of one's existence, the joy of one's existence is the joy of the awareness of the reality of that\Nwhich you really are.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.61,1:17:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you begin to own the power of it.\NThe power of everyone here is Christ-like in that by thinking of that in a loving way,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.77,1:18:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in a loving way, for our love of the people of China, Lord, many miserable,\Nand our love for the leader, see, because I found out one thing about these great leaders,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.47,1:18:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is many of them have great power, but the heart isn't open yet.\NThe heart isn't open.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.57,1:18:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The heart isn't open yet, see.\NAnd they really are concerned, and they are very, very capable.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.76,1:18:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of these people are political geniuses.\NThey're not fools, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.58,1:18:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Hitler was a political genius.\NI mean, he wrapped your friend's finger like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.06,1:18:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's out then is the heart.\NWhat's out is the intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.32,1:18:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you radiate the knowingness of that, the divinity of that intention,\Nthen you're inviting that beingness to respond to your love.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.51,1:18:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And against love, there is no defense.\NAgainst coercion, there's many defenses.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.54,1:18:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So to try to coerce the Chinese into the American way is absurd.\NAnd of course, the leader of China is telling me, what's his name, the interviewer there,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.97,1:18:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he said, what's his name again?\NWallace.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.97,1:18:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Wallace.\NWallace.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.97,1:19:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's like criticizing China, huh?\NChina, thousands and thousands of years old, and here's Mike Wallace telling this guy,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.91,1:19:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,why don't you folks straighten up, you know what I mean?\NAnd the leader of China looks at Wallace and he says, there are many things in your society
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.13,1:19:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that do not necessarily meet our approval either.\NDrugs, sex, violence, gangs, I mean, there's a few things, graffiti that we don't care for in China.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.32,1:19:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Rock music, kill, murder, and rape your mother, and slice up your sister,\Nand watch the blood squirt all over.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.66,1:19:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you listen to the lyrics of some of these things, you say, I don't believe that our kids are listening to this.\NThey're sitting there with earphones on, a hypnotic trance, they're a little bit stoned,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.46,1:19:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're getting programmed, programmed, programmed, programmed, programmed.\NKill, kill, kill, kill, and then they go out to their video game and they kill 10 or 20,000 times more,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.96,1:20:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they appear on the front page of the paper.\NWhy did you do it?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.46,1:20:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, I just wanted to see what it felt like to kill somebody.\NI just wanted to see what it was like to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.16,1:20:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What I've been doing all day, every day for years and years, Mom and Dad,\Nand the music that are being poured into my ears.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.66,1:20:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's what the leader of China was objecting to.\NI got instantly, intuitively what he was saying.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.89,1:20:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He was saying, no, after looking at your society, we have downsides.\NHe admitted he had downsides to his society.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.39,1:20:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we have downsides.\NWe have areas in which we can improve, and you likewise, so don't be throwing stones.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.02,1:20:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What he's really saying is, those who live in glass houses shouldn't throw stones.\NBut he...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.02,1:20:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He was too diplomatic.\NWallace doesn't have that degree of diplomacy, but the leader of China held back.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.02,1:20:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He held back.\NHe didn't lash out at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.02,1:20:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have, you know, he could have taken Wallace apart, but he didn't.\NHe held back and said, well, there are a few things about your society
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.02,1:21:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that we don't necessarily want, you know, to happen within ours.\NAnd without mentioning anything in specific.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.02,1:21:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what it means then is that the man did, you see,\Nhe did...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.21,1:21:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like he did have his heart there with the interview with Wallace.\NAnd Wallace overlooked his heart completely.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.24,1:21:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He was so into moral superiority, you know, the puritanical positionality that we get into\Nright and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.94,1:21:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What most people in our society consider to be spirituality or religion is nothing but\Npuritanism.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.94,1:21:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Puritanism is not spirituality.\NPuritanism is not even ethics.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.17,1:21:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Puritanism is a distortion of spiritual reality.\NAnd it's based upon the duality of right and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.94,1:21:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we can't see the people of China as either right or wrong.\NWe see them as needful of our love and our consideration.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.80,1:21:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And certainly the leader, I felt he had his heart there.\NAnd then his heart was turned down.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.80,1:22:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have been turned on.\NI wish I'd had a chance to talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.80,1:22:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, you know, I really admire your country.\NAnd I admire your great culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.22,1:22:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've made progress in what we consider to be spiritual.\NAnd what we consider to be certain areas that are significant.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.22,1:22:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's probably not time for them to consider that to be significant first.\NFirst you've got to have a working society.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.22,1:22:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you try to upgrade its spiritual positions on things.\NIt's more the way he may be looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.28,1:22:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NBut anyway, I wish I'd been up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.34,1:22:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn't get a chance to talk to him.\NBecause I'd like to just win him over and tell him I dearly love him.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.34,1:22:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe China would have changed by today already, you know.\NBut you see, everybody is vulnerable to love.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.34,1:22:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is vulnerable to love.\NThe leader of China is extremely vulnerable to love.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.34,1:22:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my intuition.\NLet's see this.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.34,1:22:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The leader of China is vulnerable to love.\NHis heart chakra is over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.30,1:22:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,His heart chakra is already over 200.\NSo we don't have to turn around somebody who's negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.77,1:23:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to turn around a monster at all.\NHis heart is already in the positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.76,1:23:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't ask how high.\NBut certainly our love is sent to him and sent especially to his heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.76,1:23:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,His love for his people.\NThere's his opening.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.76,1:23:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,See, his opening is his love for his people.\NLet's see if that's so.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.76,1:23:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,His opening is his love for his people.\NThat's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.06,1:23:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that was Gorbachev's opening too, see.\NGorbachev, when he calibrated his heart chakra, very enormous, 700.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.22,1:23:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the love for his people, he gave up his political positionality, communism.\NAnd the leader of China will do the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.70,1:23:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of his love for his people, through his heart, that's his opening.\NAnd we pour our love into him, and he will pour it back out onto his people.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.82,1:23:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll see a transformation in society.\NWithout throwing a single brick, without firing a single shot, we in this room have
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.82,1:23:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,just changed history.\NLet's see if that's so.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.62,1:24:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We have indeed just changed history.\NWe have indeed just changed history.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.54,1:24:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NOkay, so it comes about spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.86,1:24:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual work is not just personal progress and calibrating how my little consciousness\Nis going as compared to last month and that kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.09,1:24:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual work is a response to a person.\NResponsibility towards mankind in general.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.66,1:24:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the spirit of all.\NWe're very responsible for the people in China.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.66,1:24:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause very few groups have the insight, the knowledge, the tools, you know what I'm
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.86,1:24:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,saying?\NThe motivation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.86,1:24:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How many groups on the planet are committing themselves to this little project today?\NAnybody want to guess?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.05,1:24:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There is another group committed, just as we are today, resistant.\NThey're committing themselves to this.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.59,1:24:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the difference?\NOne of them is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.59,1:24:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he's one of them.\Nthere could be more groups
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.10,1:24:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,spawned out by us.\NWe could spawn out other groups
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.92,1:24:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and do the same thing.\NMake it sort of a local
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.88,1:25:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Course in Miracles project\Nfor the year 2001.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.44,1:25:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Course in Miracles 2001.\NOur project this year is...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.22,1:25:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I dearly love the Course in Miracles.\NWe're going to talk more about it tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.92,1:25:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's 10 to 3.\NI'm not sure what we're supposed to do now.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.96,1:25:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we ask for some questions\Nand answers or what?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.88,1:25:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you want to see how to do kinesiology.\NAnybody here want to do it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.72,1:25:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Work what with that?\NOh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.47,1:25:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, well, let me just mention kinesiology\Nbecause it's a useful tool.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.51,1:25:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the greatest discoveries\Nin the history of mankind, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.65,1:26:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How to tell truth from falsehood,\Nwhich no man has ever had up until now,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.61,1:26:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,right, in the recent days.\NYou find somebody that you can work with.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.45,1:26:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's start like we're just\Nstarting.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.97,1:26:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start with each other.\NLet's do it, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.29,1:26:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I keep forgetting that I'm on even here.\NOkay, now, when you pick somebody you want to work with,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.87,1:26:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the best thing to do, first of all,\Nyou don't want music in the background.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.83,1:26:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't want to influence people with visual images.\NSo I think the test person would be best to close their eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.99,1:26:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because as you know, anybody who's read John Dinah's work,\Nif you just look at a curve like this,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.09,1:26:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,it will make you go strong.\NIf you look at a curve that goes
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.33,1:26:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,like this, it will make you go weak.\NSo even looking at something could have an influence.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.87,1:26:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No jewelry across the midline and what do you do\Nwhen you get into that space?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.28,1:26:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no jewelry, yeah.\NLet's see, you'll have to talk into this.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.80,1:27:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me what you do when you go into the space.\NWhen I say, let's check something out,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.36,1:27:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you go through?\NWhat do you do?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.96,1:27:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, I close my eyes and try and relax and try\Nand clear the line of any outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.43,1:27:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then just let the.\NAll right, now we sort of recently discovered
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.12,1:27:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that the first question, the first thing you should do is ask\Nthe person to hold in mind somebody they love.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.40,1:27:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, we're going to all do this.\NAnd I'm going to show you first what we're going to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.62,1:27:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we're going to go ones and twos and we'll all do it.\NHold in mind somebody you love.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.00,1:27:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Could be your kitty.\NI'm going to hold in mind my kitty.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.16,1:27:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I love my kitty.\NAll right, so the first thing is love makes you go strong
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.27,1:27:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is not love.\NLike hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.37,1:27:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you think of hatred?\NThink of hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.88,1:28:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of hatred.\NCan you think of hatred?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.21,1:28:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you?\NIt gets harder after a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.14,1:28:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of something negative.\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.84,1:28:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of all of those little kids dying in Africa of AIDS.\NHold that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.95,1:28:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NOkay. We're running out of negatives.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.95,1:28:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you why.\NBecause as you keep using a negative example
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.82,1:28:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to make the person go weak, you yourself are starting\Nto radiate energy to that which used to make you,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.26,1:28:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, go negative.\NYou know there are images, negative images
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.78,1:28:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that used to make people go weak.\NI used them in front of thousands of people
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.66,1:28:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in many, many lectures.\NThey don't do it anymore because of constantly referring to them
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.14,1:28:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and using them.\NTheir energy has actually shifted to the positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.01,1:28:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a group we were going to test that used\Nto make you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.39,1:28:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, makes you have to go strong.\NHmm. Strange.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.99,1:28:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the power of, of course, miracles.\NSee? Its power can be demonstrated and calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.17,1:29:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So love makes you go strong.\NThat which is not love makes you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.78,1:29:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's start with that.\NLet's divide into ones and twos and we'll go
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.88,1:29:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,through a real quick drill.\NI'm going to go and divide into ones and twos.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.94,1:29:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you that want to do it.\NThose that don't want to do it, don't do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.78,1:29:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit down and don't do it.\NYeah. I'm going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.72,1:29:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit down.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.70,1:29:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Yeah.\NOkay. Just pick a partner.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.62,1:29:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Decide who's going to be number one,\Nwho's going to be number two.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.58,1:29:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's ever the oldest gets to be number one?\NNo lying.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.36,1:29:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever the oldest is, is, is the doctor.\NAnd the youngest one is the patient.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.10,1:29:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, doctor.\NYou look at your patient.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.54,1:29:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Patient, hold out your arm to the right.\NPatient, hold out your arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.92,1:29:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NNow, doctor, you're going to press down on, on,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.60,1:29:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on her wrist with two fingers and say resist.\NSay resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.24,1:29:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist. Two fingers.\NYou see? You're not trying to push their arm down out of strength.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.94,1:30:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're trying to get a feeling for their relative,\Nyou know, strength, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.84,1:30:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You push down with two fingers.\NAnd the person, I want the patient to push back equal
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.04,1:30:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to the pressure downward, see?\NWhen I press down with two fingers, she pushes back equal
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.80,1:30:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so that her arm neither goes up nor down.\NYou see what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.94,1:30:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So the more, the harder I press down,\Nthe harder she would have to push back.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.56,1:30:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So you only, you don't need a lot of pressure.\NYou just, you just want to get a feeling
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.30,1:30:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say to her, resist, resist.\NSee how easy that is?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.00,1:30:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not, it's not a hard deal, see?\NIt's sort of an easy thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.64,1:30:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an easy going thing, see?\NOkay. Now I say to the person, and don't forget now,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.27,1:30:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,patients, close your eyes.\NOkay, now hold in mind, patients, hold in mind somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.61,1:30:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you love and doctors tell them to resist and press down on them.\NEverybody go strong with love.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.95,1:31:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, okay, patients, I want you to hold the opposite in mind.\NHold the little starving kids in Viapra.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.45,1:31:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold somebody you don't like.\NPicture your favorite pet being run over by a truck.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.95,1:31:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.29,1:31:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.51,1:31:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.87,1:31:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.19,1:31:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay, anybody, anybody who's having trouble with love makes you go strong
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.03,1:31:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and that would not love makes you weak coming up here\Nand Susan will, will, will, will track out with some .
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.91,1:31:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very common, there's a couple of things that cause it all the time.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.21,1:31:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on up here, anybody who's having trouble getting,\Nlove makes you go strong and non-love makes you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.85,1:31:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody having trouble getting that answer, come up and we'll work with you.\NNo, if your husband and wife, yeah, okay, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.49,1:32:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Husbands and wives don't work together.\Ntogether so the first question the first question really to ask me is this a good
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.97,1:32:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,person this is a good person for me to work with see okay this is a good person\Nfor me to work with with physiology resist I guess yes she is you might get
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.25,1:32:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to know because a lot of times husbands and wives for some reason don't work\Nwell together but you'll have to get a relative yes the best test subject is a
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.87,1:32:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,child a child who knows nothing about the subject whatsoever you can hold a\Npicture of something that's positive or they're sort of like this to all the
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.31,1:32:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,strong and when you hold something negative they will go weak they never\Nheard of Sadat Hussam or whatever his name is there and but they'll you know
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.99,1:32:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so children are are excellent subjects but to find somebody\Nto work with first say is this person good this person all right so you don't
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.11,1:33:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,ask a question you make a statement this person is good for me to work with you\Ndon't say is this person because there's no way to answer that yes and yes or no
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.09,1:33:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no way answer that so you make a statement this person is good for me is\Ngoing to be satisfactory for me to work with is this love mixer goes strong
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.87,1:33:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,resist and that which is not love makes her go weak resist all right so that's\Nall you want to know can you all do that
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.11,1:33:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody can't do it come up to the friends who's the work with\Nonce you have it down pat I want you to switch doctors and patients switch sides
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.66,1:33:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and doctors hold love in mind and the other\None
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.74,1:34:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you're the patient don't forget to close your eyes\Nand it's just
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.74,1:34:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,okay\Noh
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.74,1:34:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,don't you don't you must hurry up\Ndon't leave
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.74,1:34:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,very\Nvery good
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.74,1:34:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody got all three of them getting ready to work out sit down\Nonce you get it sit sit down if you've got it working so that both of you
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.74,1:35:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you go strong with love you go weak with not love\Nhave you all heard what's on his melhor
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.40,1:35:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Rusia\Nyeah but you have to say take that all right
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.94,1:35:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.\NIf you're not getting the right result,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.28,1:35:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,then try down at the signing school\Nand you should go straight to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.98,1:35:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes they're gonna get interested in you.\NThe music is really good.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.44,1:35:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Just take that.\NAnybody that still needs help, you stand up
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.44,1:35:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and Suze will come over and help you.\NShe's a very good test subject.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.24,1:36:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she is, she's a good test subject.\NNow, what is the value of this?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.24,1:36:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the value of this, you know?\NWell, the value is rather profound.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.24,1:36:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the value of this?\NLet me just talk while you're experimenting.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.24,1:36:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's so much I want to share with you today\Nand we're gonna run out of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.24,1:36:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,When I first learned kinesiology,\NI used to do it all over the place, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.24,1:36:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and the thousands of doctors all over tried it out\Nand we tried to trick it, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.24,1:36:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we tried all kinds of tricks.\NAnd trying to disprove it, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.24,1:36:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we were all trying to, you know,\Nwe were all trying to check out its validity.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.74,1:36:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I was gonna give a lecture on kinesiology\Nto a group that night.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.74,1:37:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, who started the first attitudinal healing center?\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.24,1:37:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NOh, yeah, Jerry, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.24,1:37:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Jane Polsky and his whole crew had come to my house\Nin Long Island and they spent the weekend.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.24,1:37:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They're glad they're in heaven, they said.\NAnd Jane Polsky shared with us
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.24,1:37:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,how they were using it as attitudinal healing.\NSo, the second attitudinal healing group
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.24,1:37:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States was started in Long Island\Nat the clinic I was running at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.24,1:37:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I started an attitudinal healing center there.\NAnd the spiritual, the Course in Miracles group there
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.24,1:37:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,act as facilitators and so we started\Nthe second attitudinal healing center.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.24,1:37:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And to help us get it started,\Nwe had Jerry Jane Polsky and his staff
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.24,1:37:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,come and train us and share with us\Nwhat he knew about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.07,1:38:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one night I was gonna give a lecture on kinesiology\Nand I was in my office in Long Island,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.39,1:38:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a huge clinic there.\NAnd some of my friends who were doing
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.39,1:38:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the Course in Miracles were in another adjoining room.\NSo, I had a break between patients and I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.58,1:38:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I gotta give a lecture on kinesiology tonight\Nand I need a couple of volunteers.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.16,1:38:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you folks?\NSo, I had two or three of them and I knew them
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.16,1:38:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I tried the standard things\Nfor which kinesiology was first used.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.16,1:38:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluorescent lights make you go weak.\NWhat are the common things?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.16,1:38:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Pesticides make you go weak.\NAll these things that make you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.16,1:38:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, I was testing out some of these people\Nand they happened to be working
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.16,1:38:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in the attitudinal healing center.\NAnd I said, come on here a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.16,1:38:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And they said they'd be happy to help me\Nwith the lecture tonight, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.16,1:38:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I would have them look at the fluorescent light\Nand they didn't go weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.16,1:38:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, what?\NAnd I had them look at pesticides.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.16,1:39:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold the pesticide in your mouth.\NDidn't make them go weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.16,1:39:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Artificial sweeteners, artificial cigarettes,\Neverything that makes people go weak
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.16,1:39:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,had no effect on them.\NI said, what in the world is this?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.73,1:39:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we discovered that once a person,\Nin doing the Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.73,1:39:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,once you get past about less than 90 or so,\Nall the things that make everybody else
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.83,1:39:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in the universe go weak\Nno longer make you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.83,1:39:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They no longer have any power over you.\NSo, then I had a chance to research it out
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.14,1:39:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because a couple of other people I knew\Nthat I'd recommended, I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.14,1:39:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,why don't you do the Course in Miracles,\Nhad started the course.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.14,1:39:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had a chance to check them out\Nwith the Course in Miracles
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.14,1:39:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,before they did the course\Nand then periodically as they went through
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.14,1:39:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the Course in Miracles.\NAnd I did the same thing with Susan.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.14,1:39:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they reached about,\Nit's actually less than 76,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.45,1:39:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's around,\Nby the time you get to less than 90,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.45,1:39:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,all the things that once made you go weak\Nwon't make you go weak anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.45,1:40:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only subject to what you hold in mind.\NYou've disempowered
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.74,1:40:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that the world has any power over you.\NThere's nothing out there that has any power over you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.12,1:40:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can't just go and do less than 76\Nand then expect this miracle.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.89,1:40:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to go through the course.\NAnd, but we noticed by less than 90,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.89,1:40:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,if we'd taken, if we'd gotten\Nto the lobby there and grabbed somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.31,1:40:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and had them come in here\Nand look at the fluorescent light,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.31,1:40:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they would go weak, I guarantee it.\NAnd if we take the people here
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.92,1:40:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,who have gone beyond less than 90,\Nyou know, fluorescent light will not make you
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.92,1:40:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,go weak anymore.\NPesticides will not make you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.92,1:40:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not subject to.\NAnd when I discovered that, I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.97,1:40:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,well, in that case,\Nmy belief in poison ivy is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.97,1:40:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I said, I'm only subject to what I hold in mind.\NI'm not subject to poison ivy.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.23,1:40:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And it did put me in the hospital a couple of times.\NAnd I went out and I picked it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.23,1:40:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I went out and picked it\Nand, in fact, I dug it up
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.23,1:40:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and put it in flower pots\Nand had it around the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.23,1:41:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I could play with poison ivy.\NIt had no effect on me.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.23,1:41:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, whoa.\NAnd, you know, things that kill bugs,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.42,1:41:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,pesticides, sprays, or whatever you call them,\Nwould always give me migraine headaches.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.42,1:41:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to be driven home from the hospital one time\Nwith a migraine headache that was so severe,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.42,1:41:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it was unbelievable,\Nfrom exclaiming for pesticides.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.42,1:41:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, at that point,\Nalso pesticides had no hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.48,1:41:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No effect.\NSo, you can demonstrate the effectiveness
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.48,1:41:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Course in Miracles by,\Nand it'd be fun if your own group,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.48,1:41:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if you get some new people,\Nsay, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.48,1:41:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the traditional things that make people go weak,\Nfluorescent lights are guaranteed.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.52,1:41:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And thinking negative thoughts.\NPesticides.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.93,1:41:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hold pesticides.\NI've done a kinesiology with, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.93,1:41:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands at a time.\NHold two apples up.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.93,1:41:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,One is pesticide, one is organic.\NAnd have all the people look at the organic apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.93,1:41:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They all go strong.\NThey don't know which is which.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.93,1:41:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I just say, and I don't tell them\Nwhich pesticide one's organic.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.93,1:42:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I just say, here's an apple.\NEverybody look at this apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.93,1:42:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They all go strong.\NI say, okay, now everybody look at this apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.93,1:42:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They all look at this apple.\NThey all go weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.93,1:42:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Just looking at a pesticide apple,\Nthe energy, the frequency of that vibration of it
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.93,1:42:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you go weak.\NWhen we were in Korea a year or two ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.24,1:42:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,was it the first time there or the second time?\NI forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.24,1:42:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever.\NAnyway, there was a large group there,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.24,1:42:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,made up of Buddhist monks and wonderful people.\NI was crazy about them all.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.24,1:42:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyway, the leader of that group, Dr. Moon,\NDr. Moon is a former assistant to the Dalai Lama.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.63,1:42:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She was the one that came over from Korea\Nto twist my arm to go to Korea.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.63,1:42:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So Dr. Moon, without telling me anything about it,\Nsaid, here's two bags of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.63,1:42:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So here I've got this big crowd,\Nand she gives me these two baggies,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.63,1:42:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and they both have greenery,\Nsome kind of greens in them.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.63,1:42:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said to her,\Nso I hold up these greens,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.63,1:42:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody went strong,\Nand then we hold up these greens,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.63,1:42:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody went weak.\NAnd I said to her,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.63,1:43:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what's the difference?\NShe said, well, this one's got pesticide,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.76,1:43:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,this one doesn't.\NThat's amazing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.76,1:43:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to look at it, see,\Nthe energy and the frequency and the vibration.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.76,1:43:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's non-locality.\NIn other words,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.76,1:43:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,even to think of it as a connection.\NYou get that?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:08.76,1:43:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NThat's why this group has such power over China.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.76,1:43:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NBecause even to think,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.76,1:43:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,just to think,\Njust to think,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.76,1:43:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,just to think,\Njust to think,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.92,1:43:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,just to think,\Njust to think,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.40,1:43:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,just to think,\Njust to think,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.40,1:43:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,just to think,\Njust to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.40,1:43:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because even to think,\Njust as looking at that,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.40,1:43:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,not looking at that pesticide,\Nlooking at that,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.40,1:43:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it was cabbage she had.\NJust to look at the cabbage
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.40,1:43:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,made her go weak,\Nand to look at the other cabbage
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.65,1:43:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,made her go strong.\NSo consequently,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.65,1:43:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we're not confined by locality.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.42,1:43:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that he's in China,\Non the other-
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.42,1:43:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,our visual perception\Nas the other side of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.42,1:43:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,forget it,\Nhe's right here now.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.42,1:43:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,His consciousness is right here now.\NYou get it?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.42,1:43:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\Nyou think of the difficult life this man was had to be responsible imagine the
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.82,1:44:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic worry you know you got a quarter of the population or a third whatever it\Nis the planet and the whole country on your head whoa whoa how does that guy sleep without
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.61,1:44:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ovaltine I don't know every decision is going to influence the lives of thousands\Nand millions of people right you picture eternity in pain for all this whoo boy
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.19,1:44:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,boy I tell you he needs a guru to help him I'm telling you this guy I mean it's\Na tremendous responsibility so compassion for the tremendous responsibility he has
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.85,1:44:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,karmically this man is responsible for an entire nation and I'm saying he's\Nanswerable moment of death he's gonna be looking at what did I do with my power
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.10,1:44:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,on behalf of a quarter of the population of this planet whoa you know me I worry\NI see this black fetal there and he's on his back and he's looking like this thing
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.46,1:44:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,can't go around his tummy and I'm the karmic\Nimplication is that he's responsible for the entire nation and I'm saying he's
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.98,1:44:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at what did I do with my power on behalf of a quarter of the population this is profound you know I mean can\NI walk passes me you know I got to take a leaf and turn over so захid won't go
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.04,1:45:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,on I mean I might just fit I want to face that feelings coming back I mean\Nwhere were you when I needed Joe you gonna see fun like this and you walk
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.44,1:45:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,past me didn't Jesus say you should stop by and help you know what kind of\NChristian are you who like that so imagine what this guy is is handling
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.67,1:45:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,over there I don't know his name but we're going to find out his name oh\NI mean, you know, actually, when you look at it from your own heart, you realize what a tremendous burden.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.77,1:45:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, like in World War II, Winston Churchill, you know, I used to look at Churchill and think, wow, man,\Nhere's the symbol of the British Empire and its survival, really embodied symbolically in the energy of one man.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.19,1:46:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And what he was, the nation became. What he was not, the nation was not built together.\NSo the spiritual power, then, of this leader of China is enormous.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.60,1:46:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead of looking at him in any negative, there's no point to look at him in any negative way at all.\NHe's where he is, and what he's waiting for is, he doesn't have the energy, you know, no, he doesn't have the love energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.12,1:46:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's see what it is. He hasn't gotten the love energy that he needs.\NWho's that?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.54,1:46:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist. But we can supply it. Resist. Oh, yes, okay.\NAll right, what tips the scale with this man is, his heart's over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.62,1:46:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how high it is. We have permission to ask this for spiritual reasons that this group resists.\NIt's not for publication. Anyway, it's over 300. It's over 400. It's over 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.52,1:46:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 400. 480. 490. 480. 480. Wow, that's very high.\NOkay, this guy's up to 400.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.68,1:46:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,480 already in his heart. Wow, that's tremendous.\NSo we've got to hit start with him. We've just got to push him over to 500 level.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.08,1:47:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,See? We just hug him. We just grab onto him and talk.\NCome on, you old bear there. Come on now.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.38,1:47:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And we just love him to death.\NAnd he finally can't, one day he wakes up in bed and he says, oh, then he says,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.99,1:47:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,hmm, God, I don't think it's right to put all these people to death just because they don't belong to our political party.\NMaybe we should let him retire.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.90,1:47:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of executing him, we'll let him retire. You know what I mean?\NAnd he'll do anything. Wow, what a great idea. You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.52,1:47:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And he'll feel really good, you know, like Scrooge on Christmas morning.\NEverybody prays for Scrooge.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:38.92,1:47:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happens is one morning Scrooge wakes up and he's in a different world. Isn't that so?\NAll right, so we can't deny the power of our own spiritual, our own divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.02,1:47:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A Course in Miracles teaches us to own it. Own it. Instead of denying it, own it.\NAffirm your own divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.50,1:48:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,One way you affirm it with absolute conviction is when you put it into practice and see it happen.\NThat is really convincing.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.06,1:48:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It scares Susie and I all the time.\NAll right, so,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.90,1:48:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because we all come from the human\Nsociety, and it's evolution in which the separation between the ego and God is so
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.97,1:48:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,inculcated,\Nthe denial of our own divinity is the automatic position we first take.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:37.20,1:48:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I didn't, I couldn't have caused that. I couldn't have, you know, on the contrary.\NSo today we're going to re-own through our own truth, through our own, as a spiritual exercise,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.86,1:48:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,re-own our own power. That we have the power literally to save the people of China,\Nand that we will do so, and that we will try to inspire its leader through our love,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.93,1:49:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,towards him, and towards his heart.\NSo what we just got with Susie is that he, the reason that it's where he's at, is he hasn't received enough love from his people.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:11.62,1:49:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if he was loved back, if they radiated back an adoration to him, his heart would bleed. You understand?\NThere's no loving adoration directed towards him. Probably due to fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.52,1:49:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear, fear.\NThey want his respect, and they straighten up in front of him, loving him. No, no, no. It's hard to love.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.23,1:49:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody who stands for arbitrary power like that, okay?\NIt's easy to love a teddy bear. It's very hard to love somebody who looks like a militaristic dictator.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.27,1:49:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, happily, we don't know him, so it's going to be a lot easier for us.\NWe don't have any impediments of some perception of him as being other than a lovable old bear.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.12,1:50:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're just going to love him up in our hearts, and watch what happens.\NAlright, so we'll stop here.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.24,1:50:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we have to stop here.\NBut this time and then, we're going to switch to questions and answers. Is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:08.87,1:50:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody want to take a short break?\NIt's been a busy afternoon. We just saved a third of the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.97,1:50:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think we can't do it. I know we can. It's a fact.\NSee, what I believe in is putting the spiritual belief into actual experiential reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.60,1:50:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've known people who have gone around in metaphysical groups for 40 years,\Nand they're still in the same position they were.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.34,1:50:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They're still in the same position they were the first time.\NHow many times do you have to hear truth? Once. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.62,1:50:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to hear it 42 times.\NYou hear it once. Make it work once. Now you're done forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.62,1:51:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point in taking the course of miracles over again. Is there?\NThe reality of who you are stands forth and radiates from this group right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.36,1:51:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you own it, in this instant of time, you never have to ask it again.\NYou understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:06.71,1:51:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how enlightenment occurs.\NEnlightenment is the absolute grasping of reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:10.71,1:51:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And truth, in this moment, now.\NIt can't happen tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.54,1:51:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't happen next week. It can only happen right now.\NSo the real power that leads to enlightenment, it rises out of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.84,1:51:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what I'm saying?\NOut of your love for the leader of North China arises your own salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.51,1:51:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you only discover the power of your love when you express it.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.06,1:51:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You experience it and you realize divinity is that which is within you,\Nand out of which your own existence arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.06,1:51:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So our salvation, as a group here, depends on our saving China.\NOtherwise we don't know the truth of our own reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:57.01,1:52:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's put it to the test.\NThe reason spirituality has worked for me, and it works incredibly well,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.20,1:52:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is because I always put it to the test.\NEither it is or it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.58,1:52:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm tired of bullshit.\NI don't want to hear preachers talking about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:12.78,1:52:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that they haven't even experienced.\NWhat I've done is somebody on the road to someplace in history who cares.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.78,1:52:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know what happens to me on the road to going outside here right now.\NThat's where reality is.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.93,1:52:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is not somewhere a couple thousand years ago.\NIt's all popcock.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:32.98,1:52:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Experience the reality and the power of our own divinity right now.\NSo let's take a break, and then we'll have questions,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.10,1:52:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and China's enough to work on everything.\NWe'll start on Africa next year.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.38,1:53:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to recapitulate creation throughout all eternity.\NThe entire evolution of all of mankind recontextualized the human experience this afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.38,1:53:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,so we had to move on.\NActually, we did it, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:15.38,1:53:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to discuss one more analogy, and then we're going to have questions.\NOne more analogy that really fits in well with A Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.64,1:53:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It talks about the innate innocence within each and every, all of us.\NIn the analogy of the computer, you see, consciousness is like the hardware,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:42.22,1:53:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ego is like the software.\NEach of us, the hardware, you see, is uninfluenced by the software.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.28,1:53:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can play any program through the hardware of a computer,\Nand the hardware of the computer is, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.50,1:53:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,not affected by it.\NSo we're all run by our software,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.43,1:54:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but we never lose the innocence of our hardware.\NThe reason we're all so programmable, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.62,1:54:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of our innocence.\NYou see how the innocence is the opening through which
Dialogue: 0,1:54:12.62,1:54:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that which denies spiritual reality can creep in?\NIt's because of our innocence that we're programmable
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.94,1:54:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,by that which is\Nwhat you say, averse to human happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.72,1:54:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We're programmable.\NWe're programmable because there is no truth switch on our computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.82,1:54:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You can program this computer, the human mind, with anything you want on a computer.\NI recently saw a very interesting series of documentaries on the History Channel
Dialogue: 0,1:54:50.81,1:54:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of Hitler's youth, the years when these innocent young children,\Nhow they were brought up.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:58.15,1:55:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And you could see,\Nthey couldn't help but be other than they were.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.15,1:55:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They were brought up in this wonderful campfire kind of camaraderie,\Nsinging these wonderful songs for the good of their motherland
Dialogue: 0,1:55:14.22,1:55:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and the pride of their family and culture,\Nand, you know, it was fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:19.22,1:55:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How could these kids be anything other than what they were?\NThey loved it.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.57,1:55:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They looked forward to going to camp,\Nand they were all trying to be a better, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:27.57,1:55:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it was very much like the Scouts,\Nvery much like the Scouts.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.57,1:55:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that the Scouts went this way and the Hitler youth went that way.\NBut the techniques were almost identical, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.60,1:55:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,cooking hot dogs by the fire and singing the songs,\Nthe camaraderie.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:45.82,1:55:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we saw the innocent.\NYou see how innocence is vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.26,1:55:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how innocence is vulnerable.\NBut the innocence is never lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:58.67,1:56:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we evolve spiritually,\Nwe look past the programming,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:03.67,1:56:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see the innocence of the spirit within.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.67,1:56:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the innocence of the spirit within.\NSo the spirit cannot be damaged,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.79,1:56:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's when we stop identifying the myself as the ego,\Nyou know, when you stop misidentifying the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:23.34,1:56:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing I don't like about The Chorus of Miracles is the textbook.\NThe workbook is perfect,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:31.53,1:56:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the workbook alone,\Nwill take you the whole way.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.01,1:56:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing that I disagree with in the textbook\Nis the way it tends to set up the ego as an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:46.81,1:56:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you get polarized.\NYou get polarized with the ego as an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:52.13,1:56:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, your software is not an enemy,\Nit's just incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:55.13,1:56:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Two different things.\NIt's not your enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:58.80,1:57:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just incorrect.\NAnd the problem is not the ego or the software,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:03.86,1:57:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it's identifying with it.\NThe problem is not the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:07.86,1:57:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is identifying with the ego itself.\NYou can't destroy the ego, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:12.15,1:57:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to set up the ego as your enemy.\NThen you get into the problem with force, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:17.15,1:57:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you condemn the ego and fight it as an enemy,\Nthe more you strengthen it,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:23.98,1:57:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've polarized it and given it an existence\Nwhen it has no existence in reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:27.98,1:57:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a subtle point,\Nbut that is one error, I think, in the textbook,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:34.75,1:57:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is the proclivity to set up the ego\Nas an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:40.23,1:57:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's all I wanted to say about the course\Nand the analogy.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:45.42,1:57:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That intrinsic innocence, then, is our reality.\NThe programming that goes on, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.54,1:57:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that's maintained in the spirit...\NI read an interesting book.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:56.54,1:57:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard they were review books,\Nbut once in a while I get one,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:58.54,1:58:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I calibrate its energy,\Nand I thought, hmm, I'll read this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.54,1:58:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It was over 600.\NIt came from Korea,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:03.83,1:58:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was called Omniology by Dr. Lee.\NEverybody from your industry can be named Lee, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:11.63,1:58:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how they keep track of each other.\NYung Lee.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:16.69,1:58:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, they all sound like they're all Dr. Lee.\NSo, anyway, I must know 20 different Dr. Lees.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:21.69,1:58:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it was an interesting book.\NI calibrated it.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:24.69,1:58:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 600.\NAnd he said that, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:27.69,1:58:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the physical body, the mental body,\Nthe spiritual body,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:30.69,1:58:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and that part of the spiritual body\Nis what he calls the...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:35.69,1:58:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He called it the...\NWell, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:43.54,1:58:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the informational body.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:47.09,1:58:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of the...\NSo, the karmic inheritance, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:50.09,1:58:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is the informational body.\NYour karma comes...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:52.09,1:58:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit continues from lifetime,\Nreincarnation to incarnation,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:56.09,1:59:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it picks up the vibrations\Nof all your decisions, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:03.09,1:59:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it carries that from lifetime to lifetime,\Nand he calls it the informational body.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:08.09,1:59:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,\Npart of the spirit would be,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:12.09,1:59:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,like, the programming part.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:15.09,1:59:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Each lifetime, you make a decision,\Nand you come from a certain positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:19.09,1:59:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, the next lifetime,\Nyou've got to pick up,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:21.09,1:59:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're starting with that set of programs\Nto begin with.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:24.09,1:59:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you pick up your own software.\NYou pick up your own software,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:29.15,1:59:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and you continue with it\Nuntil you realize you're the hardware,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:32.15,1:59:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,not the software.\NYou don't have to keep going through all this
Dialogue: 0,1:59:35.15,1:59:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to perfect that software, you know?\NBecause if you're not your software,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:38.15,1:59:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point in perfecting it,\Nyou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:40.15,1:59:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, any questions?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:43.69,1:59:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know,\Nand I've never asked it.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:53.38,2:00:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,See, Jesus Christ calibrates at 1,000.\NA Course in Miracles calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:00.70,2:00:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't mean that Jesus Christ couldn't have.\NTo me, what I thought was,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:06.02,2:00:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,my own personal opinion,\Nis the teachings of Christ
Dialogue: 0,2:00:10.02,2:00:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as translatable into human understanding\Nat this time would not be above,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:16.72,2:00:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, 600 is as high as anybody can get\Nin this average population.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:20.72,2:00:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That the teachings themselves could,\Nhe doesn't necessarily have to teach at 1,000,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:28.23,2:00:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because at 1,000 there's really nothing to say.\NThere's only being what you are,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:35.23,2:00:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and being what you are is sufficient\Nto save all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:39.23,2:00:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, other than breathing in and out,\Nthere's nothing to do in 1,000.
